  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Response to Communities Displaced in the Colombian Amazon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim is to support the coverage of basic needs (food kits) of at least 100 families, psychosocial support for children, transport or fuel for the return to their communities, etc of families from 4 rural communities, mostly indigenous from the Putumayo river bank in the Colombian Amazon, who suffered forced displacement due to armed conflicts between illegal armed groups, who are in confrontation for the control of the territory and illegal economic activities. In addition, it is planned to accompany the gradual return of these communities to their territories of origin, once the circumstances allow it (it is expected to be in the lapse of about 3 to 4 months).</narrative>
  </description>
